WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.044
♪

00:02.044 --> 00:04.963
CINDA CANNING: You're listening to
All is Not OK in Oklahoma

00:04.963 --> 00:06.173
from Cinda Canning.

00:06.173 --> 00:08.383
I wasn't expecting
to find anything related

00:08.383 --> 00:10.219
to the disappearance of Becky.

00:10.219 --> 00:12.262
- What the fuck is in Bo's mouth?

00:12.262 --> 00:13.555
BOTH:
Becky's panties!

00:13.555 --> 00:16.892
- I'm Leonora Folger, the mother of Bunny.

00:16.892 --> 00:19.102
Where the fuck is my painting?

00:19.102 --> 00:21.355
- You bought the painting
from the artist, Rose Cooper?

00:21.355 --> 00:22.773
LEONORA FOLGER:
She went missing.

00:22.773 --> 00:24.816
- Dad? Dad!
- It's okay, buddy!

00:24.816 --> 00:28.362
- I was having an affair
with your father for years.

00:28.362 --> 00:29.696
- I thought Rose Cooper was.

00:29.696 --> 00:31.365
- She was, too.

00:31.365 --> 00:33.033
- We're texting with the killer!

00:33.033 --> 00:35.744
- We tell him we'll put
the matchbook in a trashcan

00:35.744 --> 00:37.454
outside Morningside Park, and then...
[pop]

00:37.454 --> 00:38.914
twist!
OLIVER PUTNAM: Glitter.

00:38.914 --> 00:41.458
- There goes our best chance
at clearing our names.

00:41.458 --> 00:43.335
Who is Glitter Guy?

00:44.211 --> 00:45.212
[rattling, clang]

00:47.172 --> 00:49.216
Damn it! He has the matchbook!

00:49.216 --> 00:51.343
- What's stopping me from
locking you up today, huh?

00:52.344 --> 00:53.637
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

00:57.766 --> 01:00.769
♪ classical piano playing ♪

01:00.769 --> 01:03.772
[quiet room chatter]
[muffled thudding]

01:06.316 --> 01:08.360
DETECTIVE KREPS:
Last year, the NYPD had a budget

01:08.360 --> 01:10.779
of $5.5 billion.

01:10.779 --> 01:12.823
That's a billion with a "B."

01:12.823 --> 01:16.660
My salary was 85,819 before taxes,

01:16.660 --> 01:20.414
alimony, and the mortgage on this
fuckin' dump where I also live.

01:21.290 --> 01:25.252
If you divide 85,819 by 5.5 billion,
you get...

01:25.919 --> 01:29.214
I have no fuckin' idea,
but it's a drop in the bucket.

01:29.214 --> 01:30.507
[muffled thud]

01:30.507 --> 01:33.802
Try living on that in New York City.
It's impossible.

01:33.802 --> 01:36.096
[beep]
So you take other jobs.

01:36.096 --> 01:38.140
You work security at Coney Island,

01:38.140 --> 01:40.184
or you help out departments in small towns

01:40.184 --> 01:42.186
that might not be equipped
to handle things

01:42.186 --> 01:44.229
like multiple homicides
or missing persons,

01:44.229 --> 01:45.647
shit like that.

01:45.647 --> 01:48.150
You get in,
you get out, you get paid.

01:48.150 --> 01:49.401
You go through the motions.

01:50.527 --> 01:53.113
But every once in a while,
you meet someone

01:53.113 --> 01:54.656
and everything changes.

01:54.656 --> 01:56.408
You see a gal in a bar,

01:56.408 --> 01:58.660
or a guy, if that's your thing,

01:58.660 --> 02:01.330
and you toss out some Cary Grant BS like,

02:01.330 --> 02:03.832
"What brings someone like you
to a joint like this?"

02:03.832 --> 02:06.752
And she, or he, if that's your thing,

02:06.752 --> 02:08.378
they smile at you,

02:08.378 --> 02:11.381
and your whole goddamn universe
turns upside down.

02:12.466 --> 02:14.593
And that's when shit gets really crazy.

02:14.593 --> 02:15.636
[ding]

02:17.971 --> 02:19.932
- Kreps is Glitter Guy.

02:20.766 --> 02:23.018
Oh. It's ASL for "glitter."
CHARLES-HADEN SAVAGE: Oh.

02:23.018 --> 02:24.102
That's kind of fun.

02:24.102 --> 02:26.647
- I know.
- But why would Kreps kill Bunny?

02:26.647 --> 02:27.898
I mean, did he want her painting?

02:27.898 --> 02:29.733
- I don't know. He doesn't seem
like the kind of guy

02:29.733 --> 02:31.235
who would kill for a piece of art.

02:31.235 --> 02:33.153
- Money is a very strong motive.

02:33.153 --> 02:35.405
- True, if he even got the painting,

02:35.405 --> 02:36.657
but why would he frame us?

02:36.657 --> 02:39.576
- And this is the brilliant mind behind
the whole set-up? I don't think so.

02:39.576 --> 02:41.870
- Yeah, something is not right.

02:41.870 --> 02:45.332
But, if so,
someone's puppet-mastering a cop?

02:45.332 --> 02:46.375
I mean, how?

02:46.375 --> 02:48.335
- I think I know who did this.

02:55.133 --> 02:57.177
That is a great name for a TV show.

02:58.011 --> 02:58.804
[beep]

02:58.804 --> 03:01.390
Remind me that "Criminal Mastermind"
is a great name for a TV show.

03:01.807 --> 03:03.058
[beep]

03:03.058 --> 03:05.060
- What about Kreps' backpack?

03:05.060 --> 03:07.229
And what is this logo?

03:07.229 --> 03:10.482
I feel like I've seen it somewhere.
Chickens are so weird-looking.

03:10.941 --> 03:14.695
- I know. I mean, who was the first person
who looked at a chicken and said,

03:14.695 --> 03:16.697
"Yum! I'll bet that's delicious."

03:17.281 --> 03:18.282
[sighs]

03:18.282 --> 03:21.159
- After everything that's happened,
I don't know if I have what it takes

03:21.159 --> 03:23.120
to go up against a cop.
[door opens, shuts]

03:24.288 --> 03:27.207
- I know what you're thinking. "Have we
reached that point in our friendship

03:27.207 --> 03:29.960
when we can just show up at each other's
apartments in our nightclothes?"

03:29.960 --> 03:31.795
- No, we haven't.
- "Nightclothes"?

03:31.795 --> 03:33.797
- But I just had to tell you
both the good news.

03:33.797 --> 03:35.799
According to the DNA results,

03:35.799 --> 03:38.218
I am, in fact, Will's biological father.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.470
- Hey! Congratulations!
- Oh, that's great!

03:40.470 --> 03:42.806
- Thank you.
Well, no big surprise.

03:42.806 --> 03:44.892
I mean, a blind man
could see we're related.

03:44.892 --> 03:46.393
- So does that mean you're Greek?

03:47.477 --> 03:48.604
- Greek-ish.

03:48.604 --> 03:49.688
- What's Greek-ish?

03:49.688 --> 03:52.399
- Well, you know how
I thought I was Ir-ish?

03:52.399 --> 03:54.067
Greek-ish.

03:54.067 --> 03:56.320
There's no real difference.
All the European countries

03:56.320 --> 03:57.946
are essentially the same.

03:57.946 --> 03:59.656
But now, to celebrate...

04:01.533 --> 04:02.910
[wheels rattling]

04:02.910 --> 04:04.077
[squawk]

04:04.077 --> 04:05.746
CHARLES:
You brought Mrs. Gambolini?

04:05.746 --> 04:08.165
- Well, this delightful creature
kept me up all night

04:08.165 --> 04:09.541
telling me to go fuck myself,

04:09.541 --> 04:11.919
which is why I look like
Nick Nolte after Mardi Gras.

04:11.919 --> 04:13.921
So, I am gifting her to you.

04:13.921 --> 04:15.839
- No, no, no! Bunny gave her to you!
[squawk]

04:15.839 --> 04:18.383
You keep it.
- Charles, if you do not take this bird,

04:18.383 --> 04:20.177
it will literally be tomorrow's paté.
[squawk]

04:20.177 --> 04:22.513
- Oliver, I do not have
anything in the apartment

04:22.513 --> 04:24.473
that goes to the bathroom out in the open!

04:24.473 --> 04:26.308
It's a rule I have!
[straining]

04:26.308 --> 04:27.518
- This is humiliating.

04:27.518 --> 04:29.520
[bang]
[squawk]

04:31.396 --> 04:34.441
♪

04:42.032 --> 04:44.409
- What is this?

04:44.409 --> 04:46.203
- No fucking way.

04:47.287 --> 04:49.039
- That's the original.

04:49.039 --> 04:50.749
- Are you sure?
- I'm pretty sure.

04:50.749 --> 04:53.502
- And the woman in the painting
is the artist Rose Cooper?

04:53.502 --> 04:54.503
- That's right.

04:54.503 --> 04:57.047
- But why would Bunny make a fake?
[flapping]

04:57.047 --> 04:59.424
- So she could hang
the inexpensive fake painting...

04:59.424 --> 05:01.343
- Oh, and hide the real one under her--
[squawk]

05:01.343 --> 05:02.970
MRS. GAMBOLINI:
I know who did it...

05:02.970 --> 05:04.471
ALL:
Shut up!

05:05.848 --> 05:07.474
♪ lively theme song playing ♪

05:07.474 --> 05:10.477
♪ vocalizing ♪

05:51.894 --> 05:54.897
[elevator dings]
[doors open]

05:56.523 --> 05:59.526
[keys jingling]

06:00.360 --> 06:02.362
- What are you doing here?

06:02.362 --> 06:05.073
- Hi. Um, I come bearing gifts.

06:05.073 --> 06:06.575
Well, a gift.

06:07.326 --> 06:09.328
Also, I really need to have a wee.

06:10.329 --> 06:11.830
[keys jingle]

06:11.830 --> 06:13.332
- Thanks.
[unlocks door]

06:17.002 --> 06:19.630
[toilet flushes]

06:19.630 --> 06:21.131
[bathroom door opens]

06:23.342 --> 06:24.635
MABEL MORA:
What do you want, Alice?

06:25.552 --> 06:27.596
To take more of my story?

06:27.596 --> 06:30.474
To make my trauma
into more of your shitty art?

06:31.058 --> 06:32.309
- Ouch.

06:33.310 --> 06:36.563
I deserve that. I don't want anything.
I just wanted to give you that.

06:37.689 --> 06:38.690
- A puzzle?

06:38.690 --> 06:40.067
- It's a peace offering.

06:40.067 --> 06:42.444
I know how much you like puzzles,
so I made one for you.

06:43.445 --> 06:46.365
I made it with an X-Acto knife,
um, in the middle of a blackout,

06:46.365 --> 06:48.367
which may have been a mistake.

06:49.535 --> 06:51.453
I'm not trying to look for sympathy.
I just...

06:51.453 --> 06:53.163
wanted to give you context
for any imperfections

06:53.163 --> 06:54.665
or bloodstains you might find.

06:55.624 --> 06:57.417
But, if you do wanna be
sympathetic towards me--

06:57.417 --> 06:58.919
- You know, I...

06:58.919 --> 07:00.337
I should thank you.

07:01.547 --> 07:03.465
- For what?
- For making me realize

07:03.465 --> 07:06.844
that I don't want my life
to be all about the worst parts of it.

07:07.886 --> 07:09.721
I have more to offer than that.

07:10.389 --> 07:12.891
- [sighs]
I thought you'd be cross forever.

07:13.934 --> 07:15.352
Does that mean...

07:15.352 --> 07:16.603
- No.

07:18.021 --> 07:19.523
I like you, Alice.

07:21.316 --> 07:22.818
But I don't trust you.

07:23.652 --> 07:26.071
And I can't be
with someone I don't trust.

07:26.697 --> 07:28.198
- I understand.

07:29.700 --> 07:31.952
Well, if you ever need something...

07:32.995 --> 07:34.413
anything, please.

07:34.872 --> 07:37.457
You have my number. Goodbye, Mabel.

07:37.457 --> 07:40.460
♪

07:43.714 --> 07:46.216
[door opens, shuts]

07:48.135 --> 07:51.054
CHARLES: Yes, Leonora Folger.
I know she lives there.

07:51.972 --> 07:54.141
What do you mean she's "not verbal"?

07:54.141 --> 07:56.643
She was highly verbal
and a little bit mean, actually,

07:56.643 --> 07:59.688
when she showed up
at my building a few weeks ago.

08:00.439 --> 08:01.940
♪

08:01.940 --> 08:03.942
She hasn't left there in how long?

08:05.360 --> 08:06.361
Okay. Got it.

08:06.361 --> 08:07.487
[click]

08:07.487 --> 08:08.906
Under...

08:08.906 --> 08:11.241
"Celebrations"?
[click]

08:12.075 --> 08:13.076
[click]

08:16.955 --> 08:18.790
Ah...

08:18.790 --> 08:20.667
Thank you. Sorry to bother.

08:24.213 --> 08:26.215
Oh, Charles, you've been had.

08:27.799 --> 08:31.178
- Just take my suggestion,
add even more padding to the lion's hips.

08:31.178 --> 08:33.555
Other than that, this looks great.
W-what is your problem?

08:33.555 --> 08:36.058
- [sighs] We open in three days,
and it's back to being a shit show.

08:36.767 --> 08:39.019
The Munchkins all forgot
your choreography.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.646
Dorothy threatened to walk
because she says

08:40.646 --> 08:42.940
the Scarecrow shouldn't
be played by neurotypical actor.

08:42.940 --> 08:44.525
- Oh wow.
- And then the blackout hit

08:44.525 --> 08:45.734
when we were in rehearsals,

08:45.734 --> 08:48.862
and I had five screaming, crying
flying monkeys hanging from the ceiling.

08:49.404 --> 08:51.490
It's gonna be a disaster,
and it's all my fault.

08:51.490 --> 08:53.909
- Willie. Willie. You can do this.

08:53.909 --> 08:56.954
You know why?
Because the theater is in your blood.

08:58.580 --> 09:00.582
You're a Putnam.

09:00.582 --> 09:01.625
For real.

09:02.584 --> 09:04.419
- What, you got the DNA results?

09:04.419 --> 09:07.923
- I am so Greek, I could be
Jennifer Aniston's stand-in.

09:07.923 --> 09:11.343
I'm so Greek, I could go bankrupt,
and no one in the world would help me.

09:12.970 --> 09:14.680
- Wow, that's...

09:14.680 --> 09:15.681
- What?

09:17.432 --> 09:19.810
- I don't know. I just...

09:19.810 --> 09:22.771
I didn't realize how much was weighing
on me until this moment.

09:22.771 --> 09:25.107
- Well, I want you to stop worrying.

09:25.107 --> 09:26.608
Please? Just...

09:27.234 --> 09:28.735
Come here. Come here.

09:31.154 --> 09:32.406
I love you, baby.

09:32.406 --> 09:34.783
- I love you, too.

09:34.783 --> 09:37.119
Thanks, Dad. [laughs]

09:37.119 --> 09:39.872
- We're good. It's fine.
- You know what?

09:41.081 --> 09:42.749
I feel like I can do this now.

09:43.375 --> 09:45.294
- You're a Putnam.

09:45.294 --> 09:48.130
[inhales, exhales]

09:48.130 --> 09:51.133
♪

10:07.316 --> 10:09.151
[clicking, snap]

10:11.361 --> 10:13.363
♪

10:29.254 --> 10:31.548
[typing]

10:32.841 --> 10:33.884
[click]

10:37.679 --> 10:39.097
[click]

10:48.148 --> 10:49.983
[ringing]

10:51.151 --> 10:52.778
[phone ringing]

10:52.778 --> 10:54.029
WOMAN: [on phone]
Hello?

10:55.072 --> 10:56.240
Hello?

10:56.240 --> 10:57.241
[typing]

10:58.116 --> 10:59.409
[click]

11:01.703 --> 11:03.455
♪

11:03.455 --> 11:05.457
- Looks like we're in for a fight.

11:06.667 --> 11:07.751
Oh.

11:08.460 --> 11:10.045
[beep]

11:10.045 --> 11:12.548
Looks like we're in for a fight.

11:13.090 --> 11:14.132
[beep]

11:14.132 --> 11:15.843
Jesus, I need a life.

11:19.513 --> 11:22.516
[gym noises]
[people grunting]

11:22.516 --> 11:25.519
♪ radio playing, indistinct ♪

11:28.772 --> 11:30.023
[grunting]

11:31.984 --> 11:33.777
- Well, if it isn't Bloody Mabel.

11:34.862 --> 11:36.947
Where's the, uh, dusty grandpappies?

11:36.947 --> 11:39.032
- And who are you supposed to be?

11:39.032 --> 11:42.035
Rocky Zero? Great White Dope?

11:42.035 --> 11:43.996
Raging Bullshitter?

11:43.996 --> 11:45.664
[laughter]

11:45.664 --> 11:46.874
I can keep going.

11:46.874 --> 11:48.792
I love boxing movies. And puns.

11:48.792 --> 11:50.335
- Why the fuck are you here?

11:50.335 --> 11:52.546
- Just wanted to ask some questions.

11:52.546 --> 11:54.506
- Well, that ain't how this works,
see, 'cause I, uh...

11:55.257 --> 11:56.508
I'm the cop.

11:56.508 --> 11:57.384
- How's your arm?

11:58.427 --> 12:00.721
The one I stabbed after you attacked me.

12:00.721 --> 12:02.556
♪

12:02.556 --> 12:03.932
- Alright, Mabel.

12:04.725 --> 12:06.768
What kind of a stupid
fucking name is Mabel?

12:07.811 --> 12:09.104
Dumbass name.

12:11.565 --> 12:13.358
You want to ask me questions?

12:14.276 --> 12:15.402
You can ask questions.

12:17.362 --> 12:18.822
Throw these on.

12:19.448 --> 12:20.866
Yeah.
[knocking on door]

12:26.079 --> 12:28.540
- You found it.
- I found you.

12:28.540 --> 12:29.583
Rose Cooper.

12:30.167 --> 12:32.628
- Oh.
Well, tell me something I don't know.

12:32.628 --> 12:35.130
♪

12:35.714 --> 12:36.715
- You ever box?

12:36.715 --> 12:39.968
- I take a cardio boxing class
every Tuesday and Thursday.

12:39.968 --> 12:42.095
- [scoffs] You're adorable.

12:42.095 --> 12:43.472
Hold the bag. [grunts]

12:44.848 --> 12:46.350
[grunting]

12:48.685 --> 12:50.729
Eh? I know, right?

12:51.313 --> 12:52.981
- Sorry. I was daydreaming.

12:52.981 --> 12:56.360
Have you thrown a punch yet?
I just felt a slight breeze.

12:56.777 --> 12:59.154
- You know what?
- Saw glitter on your neck.

13:00.989 --> 13:02.699
- I don't know what you're talking about.

13:02.699 --> 13:05.661
- How'd you know about the evidence
drop-off at Morningside Park?

13:07.454 --> 13:08.997
- I still don't know
what you're talking about.

13:09.873 --> 13:12.584
- A matchbook with your fingerprint on it.

13:13.293 --> 13:14.795
- Oh, that's gone.

13:15.504 --> 13:16.797
And it wasn't my fingerprint.

13:19.216 --> 13:21.552
- Alright. In the ring. Let's go.

13:21.552 --> 13:23.053
- Let's go.

13:24.888 --> 13:27.558
- I am not saying
it's entirely your fault.

13:27.558 --> 13:30.227
I shouldn't have left it on the bed,
but it was cashmere.

13:30.227 --> 13:33.105
We don't pee on things
just because they're soft.

13:33.105 --> 13:34.106
[ding]

13:37.985 --> 13:39.069
Oh, hello, Teddy.

13:39.653 --> 13:40.654
- Oliver.

13:43.782 --> 13:44.783
[presses button]

13:47.411 --> 13:49.121
- I'll kill you!
- Ah!

13:49.121 --> 13:51.039
[punches landing]
[Kreps gasps]

13:51.039 --> 13:52.875
- Arm's still sore, I see.

13:53.959 --> 13:56.170
Why'd you kill Bunny Folger?
- I didn't it.

13:56.170 --> 13:58.297
- You stabbed her with a knife
and tried to frame me.

13:58.297 --> 14:00.215
- Okay, that's enough.

14:00.215 --> 14:01.925
Alright? Enough.

14:03.927 --> 14:06.722
- [sighs] See, what I can't
figure out, though,

14:06.722 --> 14:09.016
is how you were able to pull off
such an intricate plan.

14:09.016 --> 14:12.561
I mean, framing innocent people,
secret passageways.

14:12.561 --> 14:15.355
I mean, I was a bad student,
but you're just...

14:16.231 --> 14:17.774
a stupid man.

14:17.774 --> 14:20.235
There's no way that you could pull off
a murder this sophisticated.

14:20.235 --> 14:21.486
- I said that's enough!

14:22.196 --> 14:24.156
And what do you think's
gonna happen here, Mabel?

14:24.156 --> 14:27.201
You think I'm gonna show you something
I don't wanna show you?

14:27.201 --> 14:28.911
You think I'm gonna say something
I don't wanna say?

14:28.911 --> 14:30.579
'Cause that's not how this works,

14:30.579 --> 14:34.416
no matter how many stupid shit-headed
insults you throw at me.

14:34.416 --> 14:36.502
'Cause I'm a fuck of
a lot smarter than that.

14:37.419 --> 14:39.546
Put 'em up.
- Alright, mitts up.

14:39.546 --> 14:40.631
- Mitts up.

14:40.631 --> 14:43.342
OLIVER: You son of a bitch!
TEDDY: What the fuck?!

14:43.342 --> 14:45.802
OLIVER: You can't win this, Teddy!
[elevator dings]

14:45.802 --> 14:47.638
[Winnie whining]
[yelling, struggling]

14:48.305 --> 14:51.683
- Oh, th-this doesn't look good.
Uh, should I just wait for the next one?

14:51.683 --> 14:55.020
- No, no, no, no! No, no.
C-come in. It's all good.

14:55.020 --> 14:57.356
[panting]

14:57.356 --> 14:58.524
[presses button]

14:58.524 --> 15:00.651
[doors shut]

15:00.651 --> 15:03.862
You son of a bitch! [yelling]
[rapid button pressing]

15:03.862 --> 15:06.365
- Oh god! Oh! Okay! Okay, okay, guys!

15:06.365 --> 15:08.951
[rapid button pressing]
[grunting, yelling]

15:08.951 --> 15:09.952
[elevator dings]

15:09.952 --> 15:12.454
[fighting continues]
Alright, you guys have fun. Be safe, okay?

15:12.454 --> 15:14.206
- Oh, my bone! Ouch!

15:14.206 --> 15:15.207
[whining]
TEDDY: Jesus Christ.

15:15.207 --> 15:16.583
What the hell is wrong with you?

15:16.583 --> 15:19.670
[grunting]
Why are you doing this?!

15:19.670 --> 15:21.171
- Oh, don't act like you...

15:21.171 --> 15:23.090
[heavy breathing]

15:23.090 --> 15:24.174
You don't know, do you?

15:24.174 --> 15:25.968
[panting]

15:25.968 --> 15:27.761
You're my son's father!

15:28.846 --> 15:30.514
You piece of shit!

15:30.514 --> 15:32.015
- What?

15:32.015 --> 15:35.018
♪

15:41.692 --> 15:45.070
- So, the Cocotinis are yours,
not Leonora Folger's.

15:45.070 --> 15:48.031
- I knew enough about her to pull off

15:48.031 --> 15:50.242
a little day trip into the city. [laughs]

15:50.242 --> 15:52.995
[laughs]
But, I think I'm slipping now.

15:52.995 --> 15:55.622
I don't know how you actors do it,

15:55.622 --> 15:59.376
pretending to be somebody else
all the time. It's exhausting.

16:00.210 --> 16:02.379
- You pulled it off
like the master you are.

16:02.379 --> 16:04.381
- It's exciting for you, isn't it?

16:04.381 --> 16:05.966
Figuring out little mysteries.

16:05.966 --> 16:07.843
- Not so little.

16:07.843 --> 16:10.512
The world has been wondering
about you for years.

16:10.512 --> 16:12.514
- The world, please.

16:13.390 --> 16:15.559
A pocket of the art world

16:15.559 --> 16:17.895
who wanted nothing to do with me

16:17.895 --> 16:19.605
before I went missing.

16:21.106 --> 16:23.901
- Did you go into hiding
because my father was threatening you?

16:24.776 --> 16:26.778
I don't know a lot about my father,

16:27.863 --> 16:29.865
but I don't think he was a good man.

16:31.033 --> 16:34.077
And it has haunted me my whole life.

16:34.620 --> 16:35.662
And then...

16:36.663 --> 16:37.748
you came along.

16:38.457 --> 16:41.251
- I hope that you charge rent

16:41.251 --> 16:43.795
to the people inside your head.

16:43.795 --> 16:46.256
[quiet laugh]
You'd make a fortune.

16:46.256 --> 16:47.090
[laughs]

16:47.674 --> 16:50.010
Do you have the painting, please?

16:50.010 --> 16:51.261
- I do.

16:51.261 --> 16:53.680
♪

16:54.139 --> 16:56.683
- You're a crooked fuckin' cop, Kreps.

16:56.683 --> 16:59.478
A crooked cop who stabbed
a defenseless old woman,

16:59.478 --> 17:02.105
and you're trying to pin it on me,
and I'm gonna nail you for it!

17:02.105 --> 17:03.607
- Ah! [sighs]

17:04.733 --> 17:07.110
[sighs] You know what your problem is?

17:07.110 --> 17:10.781
You know what your entire fuckin'
generation's problem is, Mora?

17:10.781 --> 17:12.866
- I don't know. Boy bands?
- Nah.

17:12.866 --> 17:15.994
Your parents told you
you could be anything you want,

17:15.994 --> 17:19.164
and your stupid teachers
reinforced that bullshit,

17:19.164 --> 17:21.708
so you come out with your little TikToks

17:21.708 --> 17:24.920
and your fuckin' podcasts like everybody
wants to hear what you have to say.

17:24.920 --> 17:27.256
Nobody gives a fuck
about what you have to say.

17:27.923 --> 17:29.383
I'm stupid?

17:29.383 --> 17:31.802
You don't know anything about me.

17:31.802 --> 17:34.012
If I'm so stupid,
how come I was able to land

17:34.012 --> 17:35.681
the smartest woman on the planet?

17:35.681 --> 17:38.100
Huh? If I'm so stupid,

17:38.100 --> 17:41.520
how come I'm able to do a better podcast
than you idiots in two seconds flat?

17:41.895 --> 17:43.522
- Thought you hated podcasts.
- Yeah,

17:43.522 --> 17:46.733
I hate stupid amateur bullshit
podcasts like yours.

17:46.733 --> 17:48.652
Your podcast sucks.

17:48.652 --> 17:52.030
The OG ones?
All is Not OK?

17:52.030 --> 17:54.491
That takes some talent.

17:54.491 --> 17:55.993
That takes some intelligence.

17:55.993 --> 17:57.578
Trust me.

17:57.578 --> 17:58.871
I should know.

17:59.621 --> 18:01.164
- I'm not scared of you.

18:01.164 --> 18:04.418
- Yeah, well, you should be, you fuck.
Okay?

18:04.418 --> 18:08.338
Because I'm the lead detective
on a murder case where somebody

18:08.338 --> 18:10.966
keeps making you the lead suspect.

18:10.966 --> 18:13.260
That's fuckin' scary.

18:13.260 --> 18:16.597
Or maybe you're too stupid to realize
what the fuck is going on here, huh?

18:18.682 --> 18:22.394
You know, people go away for things they
didn't do all the time. Remember that.

18:23.478 --> 18:25.189
Tough guy.

18:25.189 --> 18:28.317
Now, take that
shit-eating grin off your face,

18:28.317 --> 18:30.319
and get the fuck out of my gym.

18:30.319 --> 18:32.613
♪

18:40.204 --> 18:41.455
[Velcro ripping]

18:44.208 --> 18:45.417
[sighs]

19:01.266 --> 19:02.559
ROSE COOPER:
Oh...

19:04.311 --> 19:06.230
Oh, give it. Give it, give it.

19:10.317 --> 19:12.361
Mm...
CHARLES: Look.

19:17.824 --> 19:20.202
See, there's the tear in the canvas.
- Yes.

19:20.744 --> 19:21.787
Yes...

19:22.162 --> 19:24.164
- So, it is the original.
- Well,

19:24.164 --> 19:26.166
only one way to know for certain.

19:27.709 --> 19:29.211
Wait, let me try.

19:29.837 --> 19:30.963
No, you do it.

19:31.463 --> 19:33.048
Mm.
- Pull out the nails?

19:33.048 --> 19:34.424
- Just pull out the nail.

19:34.424 --> 19:37.386
There's something I need you to see.

19:37.386 --> 19:38.679
[creaking]

19:38.679 --> 19:40.138
♪ soft music ♪

19:40.138 --> 19:41.139
[Mabel sighs]

19:44.142 --> 19:46.395
KREPS: [echoing] If I'm so stupid,
how come I was able to land

19:46.395 --> 19:48.689
the smartest woman on the planet?

19:57.364 --> 20:00.367
♪ radio playing, indistinct ♪

20:09.835 --> 20:11.587
The OG ones?

20:11.587 --> 20:13.547
All is Not OK?

20:13.547 --> 20:15.215
That takes some talent.

20:15.215 --> 20:17.176
That takes some intelligence.

20:17.176 --> 20:19.386
Trust me. I should know.

20:21.138 --> 20:23.473
[clicking]
[music stops]

20:28.103 --> 20:30.814
♪ podcast theme playing ♪

20:30.814 --> 20:33.692
CINDA [on podcast]: You're listening to
All is Not OK in Oklahoma.

20:34.443 --> 20:35.861
[Winnie panting]

20:35.861 --> 20:37.654
TEDDY: Ow!
- Can I get you something?!

20:37.654 --> 20:39.740
[Winnie whining]
Coffee? Water?

20:39.740 --> 20:41.783
A swift kick in the dick?

20:41.783 --> 20:43.493
- Look, Oliver, let me explain--

20:43.493 --> 20:45.120
OLIVER: Oh no, no, no.
You don't have to.

20:45.120 --> 20:48.373
I was up all night talking to Roberta.
She told me what happened.

20:48.373 --> 20:50.209
- Did she tell you it only happened once?

20:50.209 --> 20:51.877
- She said twice.

20:52.878 --> 20:54.129
- One night, two times.

20:54.129 --> 20:55.881
- Well, now you're just bragging.

20:55.881 --> 20:58.800
Tell me, Teddy, how many
other women in the building

20:58.800 --> 21:02.387
did you impregnate
with your oily Grecian sperm?

21:02.387 --> 21:05.516
D-d-do you sell it by
the quart like your hummus?

21:05.516 --> 21:07.518
- You're insane. I'm leaving.

21:07.518 --> 21:09.436
[Oliver panting]

21:09.436 --> 21:11.313
- He's all I've got, Teddy.

21:13.482 --> 21:15.484
If I lose my son, I've g...

21:16.276 --> 21:17.444
I've got nothing.

21:19.905 --> 21:21.907
I feel like the worst father in the world.

21:27.162 --> 21:28.413
- Are you kidding?

21:29.122 --> 21:30.999
On your worst day,
you didn't drag your son

21:30.999 --> 21:33.627
into a criminal enterprise
or cover up his involvement

21:33.627 --> 21:34.962
in someone's death.

21:35.963 --> 21:37.881
- True.

21:37.881 --> 21:39.883
But I did recently encourage him

21:39.883 --> 21:42.344
to get involved in the theater, so...

21:43.470 --> 21:44.888
[sighs]

21:44.888 --> 21:46.682
- Well, that's bad.
- Yeah.

21:47.099 --> 21:49.893
CINDA: [on podcast] Becky Butler's
disappearance in Chickasha, Oklahoma,

21:49.893 --> 21:52.646
in 2015 sent shockwaves through town.

21:52.646 --> 21:55.816
She'd evaporated just
like the man-made lake

21:55.816 --> 21:58.277
at the abandoned
Chickasha putt-putt course.

21:58.277 --> 21:59.278
♪ background music ♪

21:59.278 --> 22:01.488
With no body, and no clues,

22:01.488 --> 22:03.031
freelance police officers

22:03.031 --> 22:05.284
from bigger cities descended upon the town

22:05.284 --> 22:07.244
to help find Becky or her killer.

22:07.244 --> 22:10.664
Also arriving was one intrepid podcaster

22:10.664 --> 22:14.168
who never had a good hair day
south of the Mason-Dixon.

22:14.168 --> 22:15.294
Yours truly.

22:17.296 --> 22:21.008
Every night, I'd go to the local
bar and grill, The Chicken Chug,

22:21.008 --> 22:23.218
whose orange and green chicken logo

22:23.218 --> 22:24.803
seemed to be everywhere in town.

22:24.803 --> 22:26.805
♪ background music ♪

22:26.805 --> 22:30.517
There, I'd mingle with tipsy townsfolk
and homesick cops,

22:30.517 --> 22:33.896
[turns up volume]
working them for clues and gossip.

22:33.896 --> 22:35.355
♪ background music ♪

22:35.355 --> 22:37.274
It's amazing the allies you can make

22:37.274 --> 22:40.319
over a Chicken Chug wings tub.

22:40.319 --> 22:41.945
- I didn't see it.

22:41.945 --> 22:43.864
I heard it.

22:46.033 --> 22:48.619
♪

22:52.414 --> 22:54.791
- Yeah, this painting on top,

22:54.791 --> 22:56.668
oh, that was for me.

23:00.506 --> 23:01.965
And the one underneath...

23:05.844 --> 23:07.513
this was for him.

23:09.097 --> 23:11.099
♪

23:11.099 --> 23:13.143
The man he most wanted to be.

23:13.143 --> 23:15.395
A father to his boy.

23:23.320 --> 23:24.363
[sniffles]

23:24.821 --> 23:25.822
[inhales]

23:27.074 --> 23:28.575
He was my love.

23:30.202 --> 23:32.204
He tried to keep me safe...

23:33.247 --> 23:34.456
[sighs]

23:34.456 --> 23:36.500
from a rage-filled husband.

23:37.209 --> 23:40.379
I had to leave. To keep us both safe,

23:40.379 --> 23:42.172
I had to disappear myself.

23:42.631 --> 23:45.008
We never saw each other again.

23:47.553 --> 23:49.680
- He died heartbroken.

23:53.392 --> 23:55.644
- What is the thing
about fathers and sons?

23:55.644 --> 23:57.855
Why is that relationship so hard?

23:57.855 --> 24:00.649
- Oh. I don't know.
[indistinct crooner singing]

24:00.649 --> 24:02.943
Biology. Hubris.

24:03.819 --> 24:05.946
Good old-fashioned stupidity.
[laughs]

24:06.780 --> 24:08.782
Were you close to your father?

24:10.200 --> 24:11.910
- Well, I-I tried to be.

24:13.161 --> 24:15.122
He was a door-to-door salesman.

24:15.122 --> 24:17.332
A real-life Willy Loman.

24:18.750 --> 24:21.628
So, he was gone a lot.

24:22.254 --> 24:23.755
But when he was home,

24:24.631 --> 24:27.176
I would do whatever I could
to get his attention.

24:28.093 --> 24:29.344
Hence my...

24:29.761 --> 24:32.764
what some would describe
as "extra" persona.

24:32.764 --> 24:33.765
[weak laugh]

24:34.474 --> 24:35.517
How about you?

24:36.059 --> 24:37.644
- Fuck no. I hated him.

24:38.896 --> 24:41.315
He was killed in the back room
of a Chinese restaurant

24:41.315 --> 24:42.858
by a Korean bookie.

24:42.858 --> 24:44.276
Took two to the chest.

24:44.276 --> 24:46.820
- Okay, this isn't a competition.

24:46.820 --> 24:48.071
- I'm just saying...

24:49.072 --> 24:50.574
because of that...

24:51.783 --> 24:54.786
all I ever wanted was to have
a good relationship with Theo.

24:56.413 --> 24:57.831
Like the one you have with Will.

24:59.583 --> 25:00.918
And I fucked it up.

25:02.085 --> 25:03.212
- Will you do me a favor?

25:03.921 --> 25:06.840
- [sighs] Aren't we square at this point?

25:06.840 --> 25:09.218
You send me to jail, I fuck your wife?

25:09.218 --> 25:10.761
- Just...

25:10.761 --> 25:12.262
promise me...

25:13.180 --> 25:15.182
that you'll never tell Will.

25:16.016 --> 25:18.018
I told Roberta this, too.

25:19.853 --> 25:21.939
I mean, if you two managed to keep

25:21.939 --> 25:24.942
the mere possibility of this
a secret all these years,

25:25.692 --> 25:29.196
can't we just keep on keeping on
for the sake of Will?

25:30.239 --> 25:31.990
- I'll do whatever you want me to do.

25:32.574 --> 25:34.159
- Thank you.

25:34.159 --> 25:37.162
♪ crooning continues ♪

25:39.331 --> 25:41.208
Twice?

25:41.208 --> 25:43.210
- I was younger.
[Oliver growls]

25:44.628 --> 25:46.046
[sighs]

25:46.046 --> 25:48.048
♪ song ends, fades out ♪

25:48.590 --> 25:49.633
- Hey.

25:50.926 --> 25:53.303
- You shouldn't be here.
Cinda could be back any minute.

25:53.303 --> 25:54.471
- Well, where is she?

25:54.471 --> 25:55.722
- Uh, vocal massage.

25:56.557 --> 25:59.309
She pays a Thai guy to rub her throat.
What do you want me to tell you?

25:59.309 --> 26:01.186
- Well, this will be quick. I--
- The other day

26:01.186 --> 26:03.480
when I said that I could help you,
that was a mistake.

26:03.480 --> 26:05.274
I can't do anything else for you.

26:05.274 --> 26:07.776
Please just... leave me in peace.

26:07.776 --> 26:09.486
- Bunny Folger's murder?

26:10.612 --> 26:12.489
That cop Kreps?

26:12.489 --> 26:15.492
This all has something to do with
All is Not OK in Oklahoma.

26:16.118 --> 26:18.412
I just can't figure out how.

26:18.412 --> 26:20.581
It's like I'm missing
a puzzle piece somewhere.

26:21.623 --> 26:23.166
- You should let this go.

26:23.166 --> 26:25.711
You should go, and you should let this go.
- Poppy--

26:25.711 --> 26:28.380
- Mabel! Please go.

26:28.380 --> 26:31.383
♪

26:32.134 --> 26:34.094
- You deserve to have this, Charles.

26:34.094 --> 26:35.053
- Thank you.

26:35.596 --> 26:39.266
- Better you than that woman that came
sniffing around a few months ago.

26:39.266 --> 26:41.393
[soft laugh]
- What woman?

26:41.393 --> 26:44.271
- Poppy, what do you know?
What are you so scared of?

26:45.063 --> 26:46.732
- You don't know what she's capable of.

26:47.357 --> 26:49.234
You don't know what she'd do
to get what she wants.

26:49.234 --> 26:52.196
- She had brown hair and... glasses.

26:52.196 --> 26:53.614
- Cinda Canning?

26:53.614 --> 26:55.699
- I don't know her name,
but she was so pushy.

26:55.699 --> 26:57.701
- Cinda Canning?

26:57.701 --> 26:59.494
Seriously? You're that terrified

26:59.494 --> 27:01.914
of a Peabody Award-winning podcaster

27:01.914 --> 27:04.458
who solved the disappearance
and murder of Becky Butler?

27:04.458 --> 27:05.876
- Yes.

27:07.002 --> 27:08.295
KREPS:
Everyone has secrets.

27:09.463 --> 27:11.340
Things we've done
that we don't talk about.

27:12.341 --> 27:14.343
Things we can't explain.

27:14.343 --> 27:16.970
♪

27:16.970 --> 27:20.224
Like when you go to help out
on a case in Bumblefuck USA

27:20.224 --> 27:22.309
just to make a little extra coin.

27:23.644 --> 27:25.854
[door opens]
[bar chatter]

27:25.854 --> 27:28.232
You plan to get in,
you plan to get out, get paid.

27:28.232 --> 27:30.943
Go through the motions.

27:30.943 --> 27:32.444
Lemme get a beer.

27:32.444 --> 27:33.779
- Why?

27:33.779 --> 27:35.781
♪ operatic music playing ♪

27:35.781 --> 27:37.741
♪

27:37.741 --> 27:39.243
- Because I'm Becky Butler.

27:42.454 --> 27:44.540
KREPS: But every once in a while,
you meet someone...

27:44.540 --> 27:46.834
[woman laughs]
and everything changes.

27:46.834 --> 27:49.837
♪

27:54.049 --> 27:57.511
And your whole goddamn universe
turns upside down.

27:57.511 --> 27:59.763
[inaudible]

27:59.763 --> 28:02.266
And that's when shit gets really crazy.

28:02.266 --> 28:04.852
♪

28:09.982 --> 28:12.985
♪ crescendos, fades ♪

28:14.570 --> 28:16.029
- Well, shit.

28:16.029 --> 28:17.489
♪ Criminal by Fiona Apple ♪

28:17.489 --> 28:20.909
♪ I've been a bad, bad girl ♪

28:22.452 --> 28:26.415
♪ I've been careless with a delicate man ♪

28:27.916 --> 28:31.795
♪ And it's a sad, sad world ♪

28:33.088 --> 28:37.259
♪ When a girl will break a boy
just because she can ♪

28:38.760 --> 28:42.055
♪ Don't you tell me to deny it ♪

28:42.764 --> 28:47.436
♪ I done wrong
and I wanna suffer for my sins ♪

28:48.812 --> 28:53.025
♪ I've come to you
'cause I need guidance to be true ♪

28:53.025 --> 28:56.987
♪ And I just don't know
where I can begin ♪

28:58.572 --> 29:01.533
♪ Ooh, what I need ♪

29:01.533 --> 29:04.536
♪ Is a good defense ♪

29:04.536 --> 29:08.498
♪ 'Cause I'm feeling like a criminal... ♪
